# Square Matrix Simple

## Description

This project contains a Python function that returns a new matrix where each value is the square of the value in the original matrix.

The original matrix is not modified.

## Prototype

```python
def square_matrix_simple(matrix=[])
```

## Example

```python
matrix = [
    [1, 2, 3],
    [4, 5, 6],
    [7, 8, 9]
]

new_matrix = square_matrix_simple(matrix)

print(new_matrix)
```

## Output

```
[[1, 4, 9], [16, 25, 36], [49, 64, 81]]
```
